5:
Wow... So this is the ship you're
normally stationed on, Rain?
9:
The Blaue Fraxis, yes. It belongs to
my commanding officer.
17:
Hey, howdy! 
Sorry to keep you waiting, 
Crimson Blade grunts!
21:
The name's Fraxis, captain in the
Gaean Navy. Don't you forget it!
24:
I've been waiting for ages to meet
you all!
28:
Ow! I-I mean, nice to meetâ€”
Hey!
33:
So you're the big cheese that got
the kid to bring us out here. What for?
38:
For interrogation, of course! 
I need intel on your captain 
and my arch-rival...
41:
You're gonna tell me where I can
find Captain Marina!
48:
Wait, you don't know where she is
either?
52:
Well... One minute she's wandering
around on the beach, and the next
she's off on some adventure...
60:
Hm... Oh well. As long as she's
enjoying herself!
65:
How do you know Marina in the first
place?
69:
You could say she's something of a
rival. As a commissioned officer in
the Gaean Navy, I can't let a pirate
beat me when it comes to
pirate-hunting!
71:
Not to mention she's a great
drinking buddy! So I gotta find her!
76:
Th-that's it? I expected a more
serious reason...
80:
Like I said before, I'm not going to do
anything out of line.
84:
I just wanted to know where Marina
was... And learn more about her
crew, as well!
89:
I see...
In other words, your aim is to foster
a cooperative relationship with us?
93:
Geez, you're a stiff one. I would like to
get along with you all, though!
98:
You guys seem like the type where 
I can skip all the boring formalities
and get straight to sharing drinks!
101:
Nothing beats a relationship like
that in my book. Besides, it's only
natural I'd wanna be on good terms
with my rival's crew!
106:
Sheesh. If that's what you had in
mind in the first place, you should've
brought some drinks with you.
110:
Heh, tough crowd. I'll bring the good
stuff next time, don't you worry!
115: Just juice for Stella and I, thank you.
119:
You got it! We'll drink until the sun
comes up!
131:
Tough break, Rain. Time to get to
work!
140:
Don't worry, we can handle this one
ourselves.
143:
But since you're here, you might as
well have a front-row seat to our
heroics!
147:
Hah, what a haul! We best be gettin'
out of hereâ€”
150: B-boss! That ship! It's coming for us!
160:
Let me make something clear! It's
not you pirates who call the shots
on these waters...
162:
Because nobody's competing with
firepower like this!
169:
C-Captain! Our other ships are
being ripped apartâ€”
173:
F-forget them! Retreat! Full speed
ahead!
177:
Ohoho! Great shooting, 
you're hammering them!
181:
Looks like their dog of a captain is
making a break for it. Time to go to
work!
189:
Heh-heh. You're a good kid, Rain! 
But I've got this!
192:
Watch closely and you might learn
a thing or two!
195:
What are you fools doing?! 
I said RETREAT!
198:
Wow, they really think they've got a
chance!
201:
Looks like I've gotta show them how
the Navy feels about piracy.
204:
They'll never cause trouble on these
waters again!
210:
Wow... I hardly had time to figure out
what was happening before you
were done with them.
214:
Heh-heh. Right? I take my job
seriously, after all!
217:
...I am feeling a little on-edge,
though.
221:
I hate to end things here, but it's
time for me to go.
224:
Take good care of Rain, eh? If he's
going to be seeing other worlds, he
might as well make the most of it!
229: So you're quite familiar with us, then.
233:
Don't worry, Rain didn't blab. I've got
my own methods of getting intel on
people, you know!
236:
...Anyway, if you see Marina, tell her
to come pay me a visit sometime,
will you?
239: Tell her I was looking reeeal furious!
244:
You'll definitely see her if you come
to Starview Village.
253:
As long as we can skip the boring
formalities.
257:
Ha! Nothing's better than making
new friends!
261:
I'll stop by once I can find some
souvenirs to bring with me. Looking
forward to it!
